{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1067,"text":"I made a film that was impossible to make,"},{"time":3952,"text":"but I didn't know it was impossible,"},{"time":7603,"text":"and that's how I was able to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10395,"text":"\"Mars et Avril\" is a science fiction film."},{"time":12855,"text":"It's set in Montreal some 50 years in the future."},{"time":17053,"text":"No one had done that kind of movie in Quebec before"},{"time":19255,"text":"because it's expensive, it's set in the future,"},{"time":22937,"text":"and it's got tons of visual effects,"},{"time":24597,"text":"and it's shot on green screen."},{"time":27028,"text":"Yet this is the kind of movie that I wanted to make"},{"time":29179,"text":"ever since I was a kid, really,"},{"time":31164,"text":"back when I was reading some comic books"},{"time":33273,"text":"and dreaming about what the future might be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36869,"text":"When American producers see my film,"},{"time":39505,"text":"they think that I had a big budget to do it,"},{"time":42789,"text":"like 23 million."},{"time":45908,"text":"But in fact I had 10 percent of that budget."},{"time":48894,"text":"I did \"Mars et Avril\" for only 2.3 million."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51443,"text":"So you might wonder, what's the deal here?"},{"time":52539,"text":"How did I do this?"},{"time":55092,"text":"Well, it's two things. First, it's time."},{"time":58329,"text":"When you don't have money, you must take time,"},{"time":61110,"text":"and it took me seven years to do \"Mars et Avril.\""},{"time":65002,"text":"The second aspect is love."},{"time":68332,"text":"I got tons and tons of generosity from everyone involved."},{"time":71870,"text":"And it seems like every department had nothing,"},{"time":74040,"text":"so they had to rely on our creativity"},{"time":77068,"text":"and turn every problem into an opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79642,"text":"And that brings me to the point of my talk, actually,"},{"time":81668,"text":"how constraints, big creative constraints, can boost creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85808,"text":"But let me go back in time a bit."},{"time":89216,"text":"In my early 20s, I did some graphic novels,"},{"time":92373,"text":"but they weren't your usual graphic novels."},{"time":94407,"text":"They were books telling a science fiction story"},{"time":96900,"text":"through images and text,"},{"time":99605,"text":"and most of the actors who are now starring"},{"time":103188,"text":"in the movie adaptation, they were already involved"},{"time":105246,"text":"in these books portraying characters"},{"time":108840,"text":"into a sort of experimental, theatrical, simplistic way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114387,"text":"And one of these actors is the great stage director"},{"time":118090,"text":"and actor Robert Lepage."},{"time":119534,"text":"And I just love this guy."},{"time":121055,"text":"I've been in love with this guy since I was a kid."},{"time":124500,"text":"His career I admire a lot."},{"time":127303,"text":"And I wanted this guy to be involved in my crazy project,"},{"time":130236,"text":"and he was kind enough to lend his image"},{"time":134396,"text":"to the character of Eugène Spaak,"},{"time":136059,"text":"who is a cosmologist and artist who seeks relation"},{"time":140681,"text":"in between time, space, love, music and women."},{"time":146151,"text":"And he was a perfect fit for the part,"},{"time":149706,"text":"and Robert is actually the one who gave me my first chance."},{"time":152890,"text":"He was the one who believed in me"},{"time":155226,"text":"and encouraged me to do an adaptation of my books"},{"time":158803,"text":"into a film, and to write, direct,"},{"time":161758,"text":"and produce the film myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163810,"text":"And Robert is actually the very first example"},{"time":167620,"text":"of how constraints can boost creativity."},{"time":171504,"text":"Because this guy is the busiest man on the planet."},{"time":174171,"text":"I mean, his agenda is booked until 2042,"},{"time":177294,"text":"and he's really hard to get,"},{"time":181134,"text":"and I wanted him to be in the movie,"},{"time":184017,"text":"to reprise his role in the movie."},{"time":185922,"text":"But the thing is, had I waited"},{"time":188918,"text":"for him until 2042, my film wouldn't be"},{"time":191470,"text":"a futuristic film anymore, so I just couldn't do that. Right?"},{"time":195266,"text":"But that's kind of a big problem."},{"time":196950,"text":"How do you get somebody who is too busy"},{"time":200243,"text":"to star in a movie?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202369,"text":"Well, I said as a joke in a production meeting --"},{"time":206271,"text":"and this is a true story, by the way —"},{"time":208016,"text":"I said, \"Why don't we turn this guy into a hologram?"},{"time":210928,"text":"Because, you know, he is everywhere"},{"time":213091,"text":"and nowhere on the planet at the same time,"},{"time":214957,"text":"and he's an illuminated being in my mind,"},{"time":217528,"text":"and he's in between reality and virtual reality,"},{"time":221782,"text":"so it would make perfect sense"},{"time":223756,"text":"to turn this guy into a hologram.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":226006,"text":"Everybody around the table laughed,"},{"time":228326,"text":"but the joke was kind of a good solution,"},{"time":230862,"text":"so that's what we ended up doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233318,"text":"Here's how we did it. We shot Robert with six cameras."},{"time":237021,"text":"He was dressed in green and he was like"},{"time":239463,"text":"in a green aquarium."},{"time":241207,"text":"Each camera was covering 60 degrees of his head,"},{"time":243985,"text":"so that in post-production we could use"},{"time":246598,"text":"pretty much any angle we needed,"},{"time":248490,"text":"and we shot only his head."},{"time":250902,"text":"Six months later there was a guy on set,"},{"time":253408,"text":"a mime portraying the body,"},{"time":255238,"text":"the vehicle for the head."},{"time":257678,"text":"And he was wearing a green hood"},{"time":260929,"text":"so that we could erase the green hood in postproduction"},{"time":264111,"text":"and replace it with Robert Lepage's head."},{"time":266398,"text":"So he became like a renaissance man,"},{"time":268406,"text":"and here's what it looks like in the movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270456,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282776,"text":"(Video) Robert Lepage: [As usual, Arthur's drawing"},{"time":284944,"text":"didn't account for the technical challenges."},{"time":287138,"text":"I welded the breech, but the valve is still gaping."},{"time":291081,"text":"I tried to lift the pallets to lower the pressure in the sound box,"},{"time":295364,"text":"but I might have hit a heartstring."},{"time":299296,"text":"It still sounds too low.]"},{"time":301678,"text":"Jacques Languirand: [That's normal."},{"time":302609,"text":"The instrument always ends up resembling its model.]"},{"time":305771,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":326266,"text":"Martin Villeneuve: Now these musical instruments"},{"time":329684,"text":"that you see in this excerpt,"},{"time":331828,"text":"they're my second example of how"},{"time":334335,"text":"constraints can boost creativity,"},{"time":336727,"text":"because I desperately needed these objects in my movie."},{"time":339947,"text":"They are objects of desire."},{"time":341648,"text":"They are imaginary musical instruments."},{"time":344043,"text":"And they carry a nice story with them."},{"time":346123,"text":"Actually, I knew what these things would look like"},{"time":350777,"text":"in my mind for many, many years."},{"time":352607,"text":"But my problem was, I didn't have the money"},{"time":356820,"text":"to pay for them. I couldn't afford them."},{"time":359601,"text":"So that's kind of a big problem too."},{"time":362032,"text":"How do you get something that you can't afford?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365633,"text":"And, you know, I woke up one morning with a pretty good idea."},{"time":369593,"text":"I said, \"What if I have somebody else pay for them?\""},{"time":373756,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376617,"text":"But who on Earth would be interested"},{"time":380345,"text":"by seven not-yet-built musical instruments"},{"time":383561,"text":"inspired by women's bodies?"},{"time":385261,"text":"And I thought of Cirque du Soleil in Montreal,"},{"time":388175,"text":"because who better to understand the kind of"},{"time":391533,"text":"crazy poetry that I wanted to put on screen?"},{"time":394212,"text":"So I found my way to Guy Laliberté, Cirque du Soleil's CEO,"},{"time":397386,"text":"and I presented my crazy idea to him"},{"time":400154,"text":"with sketches like this and visual references,"},{"time":403388,"text":"and something pretty amazing happened."},{"time":406115,"text":"Guy was interested by this idea"},{"time":408466,"text":"not because I was asking for his money,"},{"time":411771,"text":"but because I came to him with a good idea"},{"time":415197,"text":"in which everybody was happy."},{"time":416919,"text":"It was kind of a perfect triangle"},{"time":419028,"text":"in which the art buyer was happy"},{"time":422515,"text":"because he got the instruments at a cheaper price,"},{"time":425455,"text":"because they weren't even made."},{"time":427328,"text":"He took a leap of faith."},{"time":428937,"text":"And the artist, Dominique Engel, brilliant guy,"},{"time":432794,"text":"he was happy too because he had a dream project"},{"time":435623,"text":"to work on for a year."},{"time":437104,"text":"And obviously I was happy because I got the instruments"},{"time":440918,"text":"in my film for free, which was kind of what I tried to do."},{"time":445726,"text":"So here they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447444,"text":"And my last example of how constraints"},{"time":450918,"text":"can boost creativity"},{"time":452427,"text":"comes from the green,"},{"time":456037,"text":"because this is a weird color, a crazy color,"},{"time":459880,"text":"and you need to replace the green screens eventually"},{"time":462942,"text":"and you must figure that out sooner rather than later."},{"time":465763,"text":"And I had, again, pretty much, ideas in my mind"},{"time":469936,"text":"as to what the world would be,"},{"time":471952,"text":"but then again I turned to my childhood imagination"},{"time":477030,"text":"and went to the work of Belgian comic book master"},{"time":480593,"text":"François Schuiten in Belgium."},{"time":483241,"text":"And this guy is another guy I admire a lot,"},{"time":486561,"text":"and I wanted him to be involved in the movie"},{"time":489033,"text":"as a production designer."},{"time":491281,"text":"But people told me, you know, Martin, it's impossible,"},{"time":493618,"text":"the guy is too busy and he will say no."},{"time":496305,"text":"Well, I said, you know what, instead of mimicking his style,"},{"time":500159,"text":"I might as well call the real guy and ask him,"},{"time":502158,"text":"and I sent him my books,"},{"time":504834,"text":"and he answered that he was interested"},{"time":506857,"text":"in working on the film with me"},{"time":508678,"text":"because he could be a big fish in a small aquarium."},{"time":512862,"text":"In other words, there was space for him to dream with me."},{"time":516756,"text":"So here I was with one of my childhood heroes,"},{"time":519590,"text":"drawing every single frame that's in the film"},{"time":522535,"text":"to turn that into Montreal in the future."},{"time":525749,"text":"And it was an amazing collaboration"},{"time":527873,"text":"to work with this great artist whom I admire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530526,"text":"But then, you know, eventually you have to turn"},{"time":534214,"text":"all these drawings into reality."},{"time":536238,"text":"So, again, my solution was to aim"},{"time":539367,"text":"for the best possible artist that I could think of."},{"time":542474,"text":"And there's this guy in Montreal, another Quebecois"},{"time":545875,"text":"called Carlos Monzon, and he's a very good VFX artist."},{"time":549857,"text":"This guy had been lead compositor on such films"},{"time":553339,"text":"as \"Avatar\" and \"Star Trek\" and \"Transformers,\""},{"time":556286,"text":"and other unknown projects like this,"},{"time":558519,"text":"and I knew he was the perfect fit for the job,"},{"time":561433,"text":"and I had to convince him,"},{"time":562976,"text":"and, instead of working on the next Spielberg movie,"},{"time":566407,"text":"he accepted to work on mine."},{"time":568463,"text":"Why? Because I offered him a space to dream."},{"time":572250,"text":"So if you don't have money to offer to people,"},{"time":575664,"text":"you must strike their imagination with something"},{"time":578879,"text":"as nice as you can think of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581391,"text":"So this is what happened on this movie,"},{"time":583767,"text":"and that's how it got made,"},{"time":585108,"text":"and we went to this very nice postproduction company"},{"time":588239,"text":"in Montreal called Vision Globale,"},{"time":590311,"text":"and they lent their 60 artists to work full time"},{"time":594948,"text":"for six months to do this crazy film."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597894,"text":"So I want to tell you that, if you have some crazy ideas"},{"time":602683,"text":"in your mind, and that people tell you"},{"time":604356,"text":"that it's impossible to make,"},{"time":605843,"text":"well, that's an even better reason to want to do it,"},{"time":608438,"text":"because people have a tendency"},{"time":610538,"text":"to see the problems rather than the final result,"},{"time":613869,"text":"whereas if you start to deal with problems"},{"time":616651,"text":"as being your allies rather than your opponents,"},{"time":619453,"text":"life will start to dance with you"},{"time":621964,"text":"in the most amazing way."},{"time":623520,"text":"I have experienced it."},{"time":625208,"text":"And you might end up doing some crazy projects,"},{"time":628267,"text":"and who knows, you might even end up"},{"time":631206,"text":"going to Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633470,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635171,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}